Package io.xmljim.algorithms.model

Interface Vector<T>

Type Parameters:
T - The value type
All Superinterfaces:
Iterable<T>, NamedEntity, VariableEntity
All Known Subinterfaces:
ScalarVector
public interface Vector<T>
extends VariableEntity, Iterable<T>
A sequence of values. Values can be accessed by position or through streams, and also contain helper methods for sorting and splicing. The vector is "storage-agnostic", meaning that it leaves that to the specific implementation (e.g., arrays, lists, sets) to address.
